jsl.modeling.elements.queue
Class FIFODiscipline

java.lang.Object
  jsl.modeling.ModelElement
      jsl.modeling.elements.queue.QueueDiscipline
          jsl.modeling.elements.queue.FIFODiscipline
All Implemented Interfaces:
ObservableIfc, ControllableIfc, IdentityIfc, ResponseAndControlIfc, ResponseMakerIfc
public class FIFODiscipline
extends QueueDiscipline

The FIFODiscipline provides a mechanism to the Queue object for ordering the elements according to the first in, first out rule.

peekNext

Returns a reference to the next QObjectIfc to be removed from the queue according to the FIFO discipline. The item is not removed from the list.

switchFrom

protected void switchFrom(List<QObject> list,
                          QueueDiscipline currentDiscipline)
Provides a "hook" method to be called when switching from one discpline to another The implementor should use this method to ensure that the underlying queue is in a state that allows it to be managed by this queue discipline. Since fifo can be applied from any queue state this method performs no operation.

Specified by:
switchFrom in class QueueDiscipline
Parameters:
list - The list for which the next item will be removed
currentDiscipline - The queueing discpline that is currently managing the queue
